# 3. Functional Requirements

# 3.1 Authentication Service

## Description

Handles user authentication and authorization.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-AUTH-1: User Registration

The system shall allow users to create accounts using:

* Name
* Email
* Password
* Role

### FR-AUTH-2: Password Security

The system shall hash passwords before storing them.

### FR-AUTH-3: User Login

The system shall authenticate users using email and password.

### FR-AUTH-4: JWT Issuance

The system shall issue JWT tokens after successful authentication.

### FR-AUTH-5: Role-Based Authorization

The system shall enforce role-based access control.

---

# 3.2 Event Service

## Description

Handles event creation and management operations.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-EVENT-1: Create Event

Organizers shall be able to create events containing:

* Title
* Description
* Capacity
* Date
* Location

### FR-EVENT-2: Update Event

Organizers shall be able to modify event details.

### FR-EVENT-3: Cancel Event

Organizers shall be able to cancel events.

### FR-EVENT-4: Capacity Validation

The system shall prevent reducing event capacity below active registrations.

### FR-EVENT-5: Event Retrieval

Users shall be able to retrieve event information.

### FR-EVENT-6: Registration Status Validation

The system shall prevent registrations against canceled events.

---

# 3.3 Registration Service

## Description

Handles attendee registrations and registration constraints.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-REG-1: Register for Event

Attendees shall be able to register for events.

### FR-REG-2: Duplicate Registration Prevention

The system shall prevent duplicate attendee registrations for the same event.

### FR-REG-3: Capacity Enforcement

The system shall reject registrations when event capacity is full.

### FR-REG-4: Cancel Registration

Attendees shall be able to cancel their own registrations.

### FR-REG-5: Registration Count Retrieval

The service shall expose internal APIs for retrieving registration counts.

### FR-REG-6: Attendee List Retrieval

The service shall expose attendee lists for organizers.

---

# 3.4 Notification Service

## Description

Handles notification generation and persistence.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-NOTIF-1: Notification Creation

The system shall generate notifications for relevant event operations.

### FR-NOTIF-2: Notification Persistence

Notifications shall be stored in the database.

### FR-NOTIF-3: Read Status Tracking

The system shall track whether notifications are read.

### FR-NOTIF-4: Event-Based Notifications

Notifications shall be generated for:

* Event updates
* Event cancellations
* Registration actions

### FR-NOTIF-5: Subscriber Extensibility

The notification architecture shall support adding new subscribers without modifying publisher logic.

---

# 3.5 API Gateway

## Description

Acts as the single entry point for external requests.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-GATEWAY-1: Route Requests

The gateway shall route requests to appropriate services.

### FR-GATEWAY-2: Load-Balanced Routing

The gateway shall support discovery-based routing using Eureka.

### FR-GATEWAY-3: JWT Validation

The gateway shall validate JWT tokens before forwarding requests.

---

# 3.6 Service Discovery

## Functional Requirements

### FR-EUREKA-1: Service Registration

All services shall register with Eureka automatically.

### FR-EUREKA-2: Service Lookup

Services shall resolve each other using logical service names.

