# 5. Non-Functional Requirements

# 5.1 Security Requirements

### NFR-SEC-1

All external APIs shall require JWT authentication.

### NFR-SEC-2

Internal APIs shall require X-Service-Token validation.

### NFR-SEC-3

Passwords shall never be stored in plain text.

### NFR-SEC-4

Services shall operate statelessly.

---

# 5.2 Performance Requirements

### NFR-PERF-1

Gateway routing latency shall remain minimal under normal load.

### NFR-PERF-2

Services shall support concurrent requests independently.

### NFR-PERF-3

Database indexing shall be used for high-frequency lookup fields.

---

# 5.3 Reliability Requirements

### NFR-REL-1

Services shall restart independently if failures occur.

### NFR-REL-2

Docker health checks shall ensure service readiness.

### NFR-REL-3

Centralized validation shall reduce inconsistent system states.

---

# 5.4 Scalability Requirements

### NFR-SCALE-1

Each service shall be independently scalable.

### NFR-SCALE-2

Additional notification subscribers shall be supported without architectural changes.

### NFR-SCALE-3

Gateway routing shall support multiple service instances.

---

# 5.5 Maintainability Requirements

### NFR-MAIN-1

The system shall follow layered architecture principles.

### NFR-MAIN-2

Controllers shall remain thin and delegate business logic to services.

### NFR-MAIN-3

Business rules shall be centralized in service layers.

### NFR-MAIN-4

Exception handling shall be centralized.

---

# 5.6 Observability Requirements

### NFR-OBS-1

AOP logging shall monitor all service-layer operations.

### NFR-OBS-2

Logs shall include:

* Method name
* Parameters
* Execution duration
* Exception information

### NFR-OBS-3

Observability concerns shall remain separated from business logic.

---

# 6. Data Requirements

## 6.1 Database Ownership

Each service shall own its tables independently.

---

## 6.2 Cross-Service References

Cross-service relations shall use UUID references instead of JPA relationships.

---

## 6.3 Validation Constraints

The system shall enforce:

* Unique emails
* Unique registrations per attendee-event pair
* Required DTO fields
* Positive numeric values

---

